data.chText: （使大小、数量等）减少，减小，降低
data.enText: to become or make sth become smaller in size, number, etc.

data.chText: 今年新生人数从210减少到160。
data.enText: The number of new students decreased from 210 to 160 this year.
The price of wheat has decreased by 15%.

data.chText: 这种鸟的数量在逐年减少。
data.enText: This species of bird is decreasing in numbers every year.

data.chText: 人们应减少脂肪的摄入量。
data.enText: People should decrease the amount of fat they eat.
the process of reducing sth or the amount that sth is reduced by

data.chText: 今年的军费开支有所减少。
data.enText: There has been some decrease in military spending this year.

data.chText: 参观博物馆人数下降将近6%
data.enText: a decrease of nearly 6% in the number of visitors to the museum

simple_means.memory_skill: de 向下 + creas 增长；产生；做 + e → 负增加 → 减少

ex.chText: 当地政府已经采取有效措施减少失业人数。
ex.enText: The local government has adopted effective measures to decrease unemployment.

ex.chText: 公司计划减少生产成本。
ex.enText: The company planned to diminish the cost of production.

ex.chText: 由于缺少降雨，池塘里的水逐渐减少。
ex.enText: Water in the pond gradually diminished due to lack of rainfall.

ex.chText: 他的评论就是为了贬低她的发现的重要性。
ex.enText: His comments were only said to diminish the importance of her discoveries.

synonyms.bx: 指大小、数量不断减小，也可引申为贬低某事物的重要性或价值。

ex.chText: 听音乐的时候，她的焦虑减轻了。
ex.enText: Her anxiety lessened while listening to the music.

ex.chText: 进行锻炼可降低患心脏病的风险。
ex.enText: Exercise lessens the risk of heart disease.

ex.chText: 该计划降低了汽车污染的影响。
ex.enText: The program has lessened the effects of car pollution.

synonyms.bx: 指程度、规模等减少，也可指降低某事物的可能性、影响等。

ex.chText: 我们应该采取各种措施来降低物价。
ex.enText: We should take measures to reduce the price.

ex.chText: 最近宣布了一项降低犯罪率的计划。
ex.enText: A plan to reduce crime was announced recently.

synonyms.bx: 指降低价格、数量、规模等。

tr: the act of decreasing or reducing something
the amount by which something decreases

example: there was a decrease in his temperature as the fever subsided
there was a sharp drop-off in sales

tr: a process of becoming smaller or shorter
decrease in size, extent, or range
example: The amount of homework decreased towards the end of the semester
her weight fell to under a hundred pounds
his voice fell to a whisper

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /dɪ'kriːs/. The noun is pronounced /'diːkriːs/. 动词读作 /dɪ'kriːs/。名词读作 /'diːkriːs/。

value.def: When something decreases or when you decrease it, it becomes less in quantity, size, or intensity.

example.ex: Population growth is decreasing by 1.4% each year...
example.tran: 人口增长率正在以每年 1.4% 的速度下降。

example.ex: The number of independent firms decreased from 198 to 96...
example.tran: 独立公司的数量从 198 个减少到了 96个。

example.ex: Raw-steel production by the nation's  mills decreased 2.1% last week...
example.tran: 上周该国钢铁厂的原钢产量下降了 2.1%。

example.ex: Since 1945 air forces have decreased in size...
example.tran: 自 1945 年以来，空军的规模已经有所缩减。

example.ex: Gradually decrease the amount of vitamin C you are taking...
example.tran: 逐渐减少维生素 C 的服用量。

example.ex: We've got stable labor, decreasing interest rates, low oil prices.
example.tran: 我们拥有稳定的劳力、不断降低的利率以及低廉的石油价格。

value.def: A decrease in the quantity, size, or intensity of something is a reduction in it.

example.ex: ...a decrease in the number of young people out of work...
Bank base rates have fallen from 10 per cent to 6 per cent — a decrease of 40 per cent.
example.tran: 银行的基本利率已从 10% 降到了 6%，降幅高达 40%。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to grow, to make 增长；产生；做
rootsaffixes.title: cre, creas, cret

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + cret 增长；产生；做 + ion 表动作 → 共同制造 → 凝结
cre 增长；产生；做 + ate 使… → 产生 → 创造
crea 产生 + ture 与行为有关之物 → 生物；创造物
cr〔= cre〕增长；产生；做 + escent 开始出现…的 → 开始慢慢变大的〔月亮〕→ 新月
de 向下 + creas 增长；产生；做 + e → 负增加 → 减少
de 向下 + cre 增长；产生；做 + ment 表结果 → 减少
de 减少 + crescent 新月 → 渐小的；（月）下弦的
in 使… + creas 增长；产生；做 + e → 增加
in 使… + cre 增长；产生；做 + ment 表名词 → 增加
pro 向前 + cre 增长；产生；做 + ate 做，造成，使… → 不断创造 → 繁殖
re 一再 + cre 增长；产生；做 + ate 做，造成，使… → 一再做〔放松活动〕→ 消遣
se 分开 + cret 增长；产生；做 + e → 分开产生物质 → 分泌
